The paper deals with data mining and association rule discovery, which are core topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and database systems (cs.DB). The use of ontologies to represent domain knowledge suggests a focus on knowledge representation and reasoning, which is also a subfield of AI. The proposed technique for pruning and filtering discovered rules involves machine learning and statistical analysis, which are also relevant to the subfields of machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the interactive and iterative framework for assisting the user in analyzing the results suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and human-computer interaction.
